1
00:00:40,123 --> 00:00:41,625
Orabang!

2
00:00:52,303 --> 00:00:54,609
Orabang, wake up!

3
00:00:54,609 --> 00:00:57,276
Orabang, get up!

4
00:00:59,609 --> 00:01:00,777
Orabang!

5
00:01:00,777 --> 00:01:03,080
Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin, are you okay?

6
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:04,714
Yoo Jin!

7
00:01:06,984 --> 00:01:09,619
This is my fault.

8
00:01:09,619 --> 00:01:11,376
Orabang...

9
00:01:24,627 --> 00:01:26,095
Orabang...

10
00:02:01,497 --> 00:02:04,933
I can't get on a plane,
and I'm afraid of water.

11
00:02:06,602 --> 00:02:09,371
I'm never going to be able to go abroad.

12
00:02:23,144 --> 00:02:26,450
[Lesson 6]

13
00:02:38,826 --> 00:02:41,662
Did you really go to a water park?

14
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:45,583
Yes. I should have listened to you, Mom.

15
00:02:45,583 --> 00:02:47,350
It was boring just like you said.

16
00:02:47,350 --> 00:02:50,087
That's right.
There isn't anything special.

17
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:53,382
What's got into you suddenly?

18
00:02:53,382 --> 00:02:55,592
Other than something
I have to do,

19
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:58,637
I'm trying something
I want to do.

20
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:01,540
Take care of your hands, okay?

21
00:03:02,399 --> 00:03:06,536
Okay. I'll call you again.

22
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,555
Yes.

23
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:55,218
Is he still sleeping?

24
00:03:56,359 --> 00:03:57,927
Shh, you'll wake him up.

25
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:03,652
Why aren't you even thinking
about seeing Almighty Cha?

26
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,424
I'm scared.

27
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:09,299
If Orabang dies...

28
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:15,108
When I think about what happened
to Orabang, I get so scared.

29
00:04:15,108 --> 00:04:16,773
Me too.

30
00:04:16,773 --> 00:04:20,643
Almighty Cha... seems to be
scared of water, doesn't he?

31
00:04:22,379 --> 00:04:24,814
As friends, we should pretend

32
00:04:24,814 --> 00:04:28,151
we don't know anything
about what he wants to hide.

33
00:04:36,193 --> 00:04:40,822
You're only an assistant,
how can you just fall asleep?

34
00:04:40,822 --> 00:04:43,367
Milch, Orabang is a patient.

35
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:45,068
He almost died and came back to life.

36
00:04:45,068 --> 00:04:49,339
Baby, you've gotten prettier
since the last time I saw you.

37
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:52,951
I'm glad that I recommended you.

38
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:57,706
Was your recommendation in
the order of good looks?

39
00:04:57,706 --> 00:04:59,522
Do you believe that?

40
00:04:59,522 --> 00:05:03,253
Professor, did you recommend
me to make me run errands?

41
00:05:03,253 --> 00:05:05,822
You already know,
so how come you just fell asleep?

42
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:08,925
How much will you bother him again?

43
00:05:08,925 --> 00:05:11,027
Professor, you should go back and vote!

44
00:05:11,027 --> 00:05:12,729
Yes, Cha Yoo Jin! We'll protect you!

45
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:14,935
Hey, help me!

46
00:05:15,941 --> 00:05:18,283
I should just vote?

47
00:05:18,283 --> 00:05:21,571
Who do you think I'd vote for?

48
00:05:23,006 --> 00:05:26,159
Since I didn't cast my vote, who benefited?

49
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:29,195
Was it A or S?

50
00:05:40,382 --> 00:05:42,259
Miss Kim Hyun Hee ?

51
00:05:42,259 --> 00:05:45,470
You're taking break times
even with that ability.

52
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:47,009
Mr. Han Chul Min!

53
00:05:47,009 --> 00:05:50,133
Are you going to hold the bow with
fingers that smell like cigarettes?

54
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:52,402
Always keep your posture straight.

55
00:05:53,370 --> 00:05:54,837
Professor...

56
00:06:04,281 --> 00:06:06,692
You're still excessive
with showing your feelings.

57
00:06:06,692 --> 00:06:09,331
That's why your performance
is excessive, too.

58
00:06:09,331 --> 00:06:11,788
It's been two years.

59
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:13,757
Thank you for your invitation.

60
00:06:13,757 --> 00:06:16,092
I ran over here as soon as
I received the invitation.

61
00:06:16,092 --> 00:06:19,629
I heard your UNICEF performance
in Europe overlapped with ours.

62
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:21,631
I didn't think
you'd be able to come.

63
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:24,718
I couldn't possibly decline your
invitation to the music festival.

64
00:06:25,769 --> 00:06:27,603
You're still beautiful.

65
00:06:27,603 --> 00:06:29,304
You're making my heart flutter.

66
00:06:30,538 --> 00:06:34,811
That lip service only works when it
doesn't go overboard, Mr. Lee Yoon Hoo.

67
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:37,119
You're mistaken again.

68
00:06:37,119 --> 00:06:38,954
I mean it.

69
00:06:43,603 --> 00:06:46,472
These are the most beautiful hands
I've ever seen.

70
00:06:47,699 --> 00:06:53,371
These hands make people feel
excited, blissful and even sad.

71
00:06:57,916 --> 00:06:59,885
Let's have lunch together, Professor.

72
00:06:59,885 --> 00:07:01,686
I've already eaten.

73
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:06,410
But with you here, I feel like
the festival is a bit upgraded.

74
00:07:07,045 --> 00:07:10,695
Franz recommended only weird students...

75
00:07:10,695 --> 00:07:12,364
so I was very disturbed.

76
00:07:12,364 --> 00:07:15,433
Maestro von Stresemann came?

77
00:07:49,207 --> 00:07:53,411
Mina, I'm doing well.

78
00:08:00,731 --> 00:08:02,411
I'm glad, Franz.

79
00:08:02,411 --> 00:08:04,393
I get to talk to you finally.

80
00:08:04,393 --> 00:08:06,318
Only after the storm has passed.

81
00:08:06,318 --> 00:08:11,867
Mina, did something bad happen?

82
00:08:11,867 --> 00:08:15,601
The fact that you ran away
would be the worst thing.

83
00:08:15,601 --> 00:08:19,421
Mina, I couldn't help it...

84
00:08:20,111 --> 00:08:22,335
If I told you ahead,

85
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:24,213
you would've been
in an awkward position.

86
00:08:24,213 --> 00:08:28,232
I know, in the big picture,
it was for the foundation's benefit.

87
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:33,045
That's correct. In the big picture...

88
00:08:33,045 --> 00:08:34,848
I don't know anymore...

89
00:08:34,848 --> 00:08:38,985
Whether you have a deep meaning
or it's just flip-flopping!

90
00:08:41,887 --> 00:08:44,356
Let's see your heart suffer.

91
00:08:54,332 --> 00:08:55,934
Are you okay?

92
00:09:02,340 --> 00:09:04,476
Excuse me...

93
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,579
Are you going to the lounge
by any chance?

94
00:09:07,579 --> 00:09:09,983
Yes I am.

95
00:09:09,983 --> 00:09:13,523
Then... when you go to the lounge...

96
00:09:13,523 --> 00:09:17,474
my handsome, tall Orabang...

97
00:09:17,474 --> 00:09:20,870
There is a guy named
Cha Yoo Jin from my school.

98
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:27,390
Could you go and tell him
to get closer to the window?

99
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:30,802
I can't possibly see my Orabang from here.

100
00:09:31,822 --> 00:09:33,457
Orabang?

101
00:09:34,292 --> 00:09:36,367
Orabang!

102
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,403
Orabang! Wake up, Orabang!

103
00:09:41,886 --> 00:09:43,541
We meet again.

104
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:46,711
Excuse me, can you hurry up and go?

105
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:50,632
I haven't seen my Orabang for two
hours, so I'm getting dizzy.

106
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:53,313
But...

107
00:09:53,313 --> 00:09:54,827
Why should I...

108
00:09:57,362 --> 00:10:00,017
If you don't want to, forget it.
Why bother coming here...

109
00:10:00,017 --> 00:10:02,300
You'll get hurt.

110
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,235
I'll help you see him.

111
00:10:05,564 --> 00:10:06,998
Your Orabang.

112
00:10:10,602 --> 00:10:12,904
Thank you.

113
00:10:18,950 --> 00:10:20,747
Hello.

114
00:10:22,205 --> 00:10:23,832
You followed me here?

115
00:10:23,832 --> 00:10:25,633
- Pardon?
- Come out.

116
00:10:32,831 --> 00:10:36,512
Are you a koala?
Why are you stuck on someone's back?

117
00:10:36,512 --> 00:10:38,313
I'm sorry.

118
00:10:44,876 --> 00:10:46,610
Wait a minute.

119
00:10:52,861 --> 00:10:55,129
Aren't you mistreating a woman?

120
00:10:55,827 --> 00:10:57,161
Woman?

121
00:10:59,624 --> 00:11:01,245
This one?

122
00:11:01,245 --> 00:11:03,480
How can you possibly say it that way?

123
00:11:04,129 --> 00:11:07,665
You can't possibly be a musician.

124
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:26,211
- Cold water filled with ice.
- Yes.

125
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,106
Maestro von Stresemann!

126
00:11:29,878 --> 00:11:32,123
Do you remember me?

127
00:11:32,123 --> 00:11:33,879
Lee Yoon Hoo.

128
00:11:34,392 --> 00:11:36,794
You came to my recital last year.

129
00:11:37,722 --> 00:11:40,899
That famous cellist?

130
00:11:40,899 --> 00:11:42,467
Nice to meet you.

131
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:47,472
Of course I know you.

132
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:51,694
It was an unforgettable recital.

133
00:11:54,965 --> 00:11:57,349
I asked for cold water.

134
00:11:57,349 --> 00:11:58,683
I got it.

135
00:11:59,428 --> 00:12:01,463
Cold water at that age...

136
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:12,869
Ice water is not good for your teeth.

137
00:12:12,869 --> 00:12:14,108
Drink this please.

138
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:16,737
Maestro asked for ice water.

139
00:12:16,737 --> 00:12:18,703
You give him everything just
because he asks for it?

140
00:12:18,703 --> 00:12:20,250
Please.

141
00:12:31,864 --> 00:12:35,186
Let's go to the festival
opening at gala hall.

142
00:12:35,186 --> 00:12:38,256
I don't like the meticulous Yoon Yi Song

143
00:12:38,717 --> 00:12:41,803
but I need wine now.

144
00:12:41,803 --> 00:12:43,274
A lot.

145
00:12:43,274 --> 00:12:44,932
A lot of it.

146
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:47,402
Milch, I'm coming too.

147
00:12:47,402 --> 00:12:51,088
Good!

148
00:12:51,088 --> 00:12:54,717
Let's get drunk all night...
And let's...

149
00:12:54,717 --> 00:12:56,285
You!

150
00:12:57,653 --> 00:12:59,689
Did you practice your music?

151
00:13:00,739 --> 00:13:02,451
Get back to your practice.

152
00:13:03,988 --> 00:13:05,289
Please.

153
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:17,862
Now I see that my rival is not our
stalker classmate, it's Milch.

154
00:13:37,465 --> 00:13:40,885
He recommended me just
to make me do odd jobs.

155
00:13:40,885 --> 00:13:42,821
That old coot.

156
00:13:42,821 --> 00:13:46,758
I can hear everything.
How dare you!

157
00:13:47,828 --> 00:13:53,299
A pupil dares to call his
teacher 'that old coot'?

158
00:13:53,917 --> 00:13:55,793
Pupil?

159
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:58,755
You have an elegant way
of saying an errand boy.

160
00:14:01,383 --> 00:14:04,186
You should know that it's an honor.

161
00:14:05,846 --> 00:14:10,809
Do you think it's easy
to become my errand boy?

162
00:14:10,809 --> 00:14:13,686
Yes, sure, it's an honor.

163
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:17,608
It's a clear path of hardship
doing all kinds of tasks.

164
00:14:19,359 --> 00:14:24,764
Do you think they are just simple tasks?

165
00:14:25,449 --> 00:14:32,790
From a guy who digs into the full score
without even knowing his members...

166
00:14:33,571 --> 00:14:37,308
How could I leave conducting to him?

167
00:14:37,308 --> 00:14:41,404
A guy who doesn't even look at people...

168
00:14:41,404 --> 00:14:44,983
How could he conduct an orchestra?

169
00:14:44,983 --> 00:14:50,388
Why is the conductor's
position right in the middle?

170
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:54,437
To be able to see the members.

171
00:14:55,293 --> 00:14:59,775
To make an effort to see the members.

172
00:14:59,775 --> 00:15:02,151
That's why.

173
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:09,660
You're finally beginning to
look like a conductor...

174
00:15:10,702 --> 00:15:14,257
why the complaints?

175
00:16:11,555 --> 00:16:17,594
Yes, Assistant Dean. The school is
fine, so just focus on your health.

176
00:16:18,854 --> 00:16:23,158
I guess the Dean is a bit
overloaded since you are ill.

177
00:16:25,319 --> 00:16:26,987
Professor Ahn.

178
00:16:27,645 --> 00:16:29,880
Yes, I'll come to see you soon.

179
00:16:33,702 --> 00:16:36,606
Is there any word from the
Yoon Yi Song Music Festival?

180
00:16:36,606 --> 00:16:38,206
The los...

181
00:16:38,206 --> 00:16:42,869
I mean, did the students and
von Stresemann cause any trouble?

182
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:45,817
Nothing will happen. Don't worry.

183
00:16:45,817 --> 00:16:48,385
Yoon Yi Song is beyond meticulous.

184
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:53,277
I guess they improved a lot since
they performed in an orchestra.

185
00:16:53,757 --> 00:16:57,261
They can't be the level
that I think they are.

186
00:16:57,922 --> 00:17:01,063
How can you possibly come
here with that level? Get out!

187
00:17:01,063 --> 00:17:03,598
I'm sorry.

188
00:17:09,273 --> 00:17:11,323
I told you to practice!

189
00:17:11,323 --> 00:17:14,251
Only the best students who pass the
auditions come here every year.

190
00:17:14,251 --> 00:17:16,212
Of course everyone is good.

191
00:17:16,212 --> 00:17:17,869
I didn't know they would be this good.

192
00:17:17,869 --> 00:17:21,873
Look at me. I got compliments
from my morning lesson.

193
00:17:22,626 --> 00:17:25,762
From that famous timpani star!

194
00:17:27,007 --> 00:17:28,833
Get out!

195
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:31,176
How can you throw a timpani
mallet to your instructor?

196
00:17:31,176 --> 00:17:33,411
Don't ever come here again!

197
00:17:38,089 --> 00:17:40,391
What did I ever do wrong...

198
00:17:41,132 --> 00:17:45,403
I didn't mean to throw it, it
was part of my performance.

199
00:17:45,403 --> 00:17:48,806
Everyone liked it at our performance.

200
00:17:49,314 --> 00:17:53,071
Seol Nae Il, you can't get kicked out.
Did you practice a lot?

201
00:17:53,071 --> 00:17:55,373
Don't worry. I practiced the assigned music.

202
00:17:55,373 --> 00:17:58,662
Great, Seol Nae Il!

203
00:17:58,662 --> 00:18:02,999
Professor Yoon Yi Song is really
scary, so don't make a mistake.

204
00:18:04,209 --> 00:18:05,577
She's scary?

205
00:18:06,753 --> 00:18:08,822
I don't like scary.

206
00:18:09,587 --> 00:18:12,223
Do you think there are only
teachers like Professor Ahn?

207
00:18:13,802 --> 00:18:16,271
I can't stand scary.

208
00:18:23,034 --> 00:18:24,669
Straighten your back!

209
00:18:25,439 --> 00:18:28,539
Good performances come
from a proper posture.

210
00:18:28,539 --> 00:18:31,653
How can you not even get the basics right?

211
00:18:31,653 --> 00:18:32,654
I'm sorry.

212
00:18:32,654 --> 00:18:35,052
Don't answer me, and don't cry!

213
00:18:37,367 --> 00:18:40,551
I have no will to teach anymore.
Get out.

214
00:18:40,551 --> 00:18:42,453
Next.

215
00:18:42,453 --> 00:18:44,755
Miss Seol Nae Il.

216
00:18:49,838 --> 00:18:53,684
Miss Seol Nae Il!
What are you paying attention to?

217
00:19:02,713 --> 00:19:04,415
You may begin.

218
00:19:20,824 --> 00:19:23,554
Are you kidding me?

219
00:19:23,554 --> 00:19:25,814
Get it straight and start again!

220
00:19:32,755 --> 00:19:37,327
Seol Nae Il, you make a lot
of mistakes in octaves.

221
00:19:37,327 --> 00:19:38,846
Do you want to stay up all night?

222
00:19:38,846 --> 00:19:41,282
I don't want to do it anymore, Teacher.

223
00:19:43,725 --> 00:19:45,303
Go back to the beginning.

224
00:19:45,303 --> 00:19:47,296
Do it a hundred times.

225
00:19:47,296 --> 00:19:49,888
If you make anymore mistakes, you
have to do it a thousand times.

226
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:51,389
Focus.

227
00:19:56,300 --> 00:20:00,401
Piano is not played for fun, Seol Nae Il.

228
00:20:00,401 --> 00:20:02,367
It's your future!

229
00:20:17,634 --> 00:20:21,137
Seol Nae Il, Seol Nae Il!
Miss Seol Nae Il!

230
00:20:55,255 --> 00:20:57,056
Orabang...

231
00:20:59,218 --> 00:21:02,137
I finally found you!
Where have you been...

232
00:21:02,137 --> 00:21:03,681
What's going on?

233
00:21:04,223 --> 00:21:07,126
First, your hand...

234
00:21:09,811 --> 00:21:11,338
Hey!

235
00:21:11,338 --> 00:21:13,206
Am I a puppy?

236
00:21:18,309 --> 00:21:20,711
How did the master class go?

237
00:21:21,782 --> 00:21:23,750
I don't know about such thing.

238
00:21:25,035 --> 00:21:27,478
I want to go home soon.

239
00:21:27,478 --> 00:21:30,072
I want to eat the food that you make

240
00:21:30,072 --> 00:21:33,043
and play the piano with you
and have fun.

241
00:21:33,043 --> 00:21:34,778
Then hurry up and leave.

242
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:40,411
Don't be lazy with the opportunity
that's precious to someone else.

243
00:22:02,487 --> 00:22:05,256
Looking at you, I realize
how much time has passed.

244
00:22:05,256 --> 00:22:08,426
You were so tiny, and now
you're so beautiful!

245
00:22:08,426 --> 00:22:11,596
Did you just enter college
when we saw each other last time?

246
00:22:11,596 --> 00:22:12,749
When I was wearing glasses?

247
00:22:12,749 --> 00:22:14,742
Why do you leave out the braces?

248
00:22:14,742 --> 00:22:18,145
Why would you bring that up?

249
00:22:19,029 --> 00:22:22,833
I wondered, but I didn't
know you'd really open a cafe.

250
00:22:23,541 --> 00:22:25,476
It suits you.

251
00:22:28,151 --> 00:22:31,454
You heard about us, right?

252
00:22:35,564 --> 00:22:38,567
Every couple has
an on-off relationship.

253
00:22:39,109 --> 00:22:41,111
You are still getting along, right?

254
00:22:41,111 --> 00:22:46,083
Of course. Even if we broke up
we are still friends.

255
00:22:50,787 --> 00:22:55,425
Hi, it's me. Do Kyung is here,
I was just wondering...

256
00:22:56,210 --> 00:22:58,480
Ex-girlfriend? Did Yoo Jin say that?

257
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:03,342
So it's true that they broke up.

258
00:23:03,342 --> 00:23:05,010
That's great.

259
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:09,098
She acts as if she's my boss's daughter-in-law,
so I thought it was strange.

260
00:23:09,890 --> 00:23:14,327
I heard my boss's son goes to our school.
Do Kyung must be dating him.

261
00:23:28,459 --> 00:23:30,853
Is it really impossible?

262
00:23:30,853 --> 00:23:33,578
What did you eat?
You keep vomiting...

263
00:23:33,578 --> 00:23:35,446
Four bottles of wine.

264
00:23:35,446 --> 00:23:38,210
The workshop is impossible
without Maestro's conducting.

265
00:23:38,210 --> 00:23:39,678
What do we do?

266
00:23:41,755 --> 00:23:46,117
My apprentice will go instead.

267
00:23:46,117 --> 00:23:49,118
- Me?
- You were his apprentice!

268
00:23:49,118 --> 00:23:51,015
Maestro has an apprentice!

269
00:23:51,015 --> 00:23:53,309
You can fill in just for the afternoon.

270
00:23:53,309 --> 00:23:54,935
- Me?
- Yes.

271
00:23:54,935 --> 00:23:58,105
You must've studied, right?

272
00:23:58,814 --> 00:24:00,449
Of course I did, but...

273
00:24:01,108 --> 00:24:02,468
does this make sense?

274
00:24:02,468 --> 00:24:04,837
How could I conduct an
ensemble workshop?

275
00:25:00,709 --> 00:25:03,837
Yes, leave the culture column vacant.
I heard he is von Stresemann's apprentice.

276
00:25:03,837 --> 00:25:07,484
People will love his looks.

277
00:25:07,484 --> 00:25:10,034
His name is Cha Yoo Jin. Yes!

278
00:25:10,034 --> 00:25:11,535
What?

279
00:25:12,002 --> 00:25:15,097
Pianist Cha Dong Woo's son? Really?

280
00:25:30,948 --> 00:25:34,806
Von Stresemann has an apprentice?

281
00:25:34,806 --> 00:25:37,127
He's never done that.

282
00:25:37,127 --> 00:25:39,621
It was great as expected.

283
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:41,500
Where would he go to study abroad?

284
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:44,009
Would he follow von Stresemann?

285
00:25:44,009 --> 00:25:45,379
Study abroad?

286
00:25:45,379 --> 00:25:46,922
When did you get here?

287
00:25:46,922 --> 00:25:48,674
Did you see Yoo Jin?
Wasn't he great?

288
00:25:48,674 --> 00:25:51,677
Wow, he's good looking and he's
great at conducting. I'm jealous.

289
00:25:51,677 --> 00:25:53,259
I know!

290
00:25:55,472 --> 00:25:58,055
That's why I liked him.

291
00:25:58,055 --> 00:26:01,158
Now that makes me nervous.

292
00:26:02,259 --> 00:26:03,794
What?

293
00:26:16,910 --> 00:26:19,443
I heard from your father

294
00:26:19,443 --> 00:26:21,378
that you're very disappointed.

295
00:26:21,378 --> 00:26:23,665
He was worried about you.

296
00:26:23,665 --> 00:26:24,915
I'm fine.

297
00:26:24,915 --> 00:26:28,465
It's common to fail auditions.

298
00:26:28,465 --> 00:26:30,794
I had huge expectations.

299
00:26:30,794 --> 00:26:32,523
But you know,

300
00:26:32,523 --> 00:26:36,139
being in the audition means
you're recognized.

301
00:26:36,139 --> 00:26:39,436
- Just a little more...
- Just a little more...

302
00:26:39,436 --> 00:26:43,607
'Just make a little more effort.'
That's how I've come this far.

303
00:26:45,272 --> 00:26:47,037
Madam Dean...

304
00:26:47,037 --> 00:26:52,342
do you really think it's
possible if I try hard enough?

305
00:26:53,655 --> 00:26:59,594
You already know... that effort
alone can't match up a genius.

306
00:27:00,829 --> 00:27:03,220
- Do Kyung...
- It's okay.

307
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:05,834
What could I do
when I'm not a genius?

308
00:27:05,834 --> 00:27:10,636
I should be satisfied with
standing next to a genius.

309
00:27:16,595 --> 00:27:18,468
Father.

310
00:27:18,468 --> 00:27:21,115
Yoo Jin always does well.

311
00:27:21,115 --> 00:27:22,682
Seol Nae Il?

312
00:27:24,154 --> 00:27:26,676
She keeps disappearing these days.

313
00:27:26,676 --> 00:27:30,280
Of course I'm doing really great.

314
00:27:31,109 --> 00:27:33,878
Of course, of course.
Not anyone can make it here.

315
00:27:34,988 --> 00:27:36,556
Bye.

316
00:27:38,242 --> 00:27:40,869
Yoo Il Lak is a corpse
without confidence.

317
00:27:40,869 --> 00:27:42,412
But he's become a corpse.

318
00:27:42,412 --> 00:27:44,249
No thank you.
Aren't you offering some?

319
00:27:49,962 --> 00:27:51,755
Shi Won!

320
00:27:51,755 --> 00:27:54,883
- Wait, wait!
- Of course I'm doing well.

321
00:27:54,883 --> 00:27:57,778
- I'm really upset.
- Shi Won...

322
00:27:57,778 --> 00:27:59,805
It would've been really
nice if you came, too.

323
00:27:59,805 --> 00:28:02,173
You missed the audition
because of the performance.

324
00:28:03,809 --> 00:28:05,911
Yoo Il Lak, what's with this perverted behavior?

325
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:08,118
Bye, Shi Won.

326
00:28:08,118 --> 00:28:10,232
Someone might think I'm a pervert.

327
00:28:10,232 --> 00:28:12,150
You said it before you hung up, right?

328
00:28:12,150 --> 00:28:14,144
- You did, didn't you?
- What do you mean?

329
00:28:14,144 --> 00:28:15,670
Call her back and tell
her I'm not a pervert.

330
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:17,161
She might have misunderstood.

331
00:28:17,161 --> 00:28:18,657
Misunderstood what?

332
00:28:18,657 --> 00:28:20,459
Hey!

333
00:28:22,202 --> 00:28:24,337
Would Shi Won like perverts?

334
00:28:25,008 --> 00:28:26,996
No!

335
00:28:26,996 --> 00:28:28,531
Hey!

336
00:28:33,755 --> 00:28:35,340
What did he say?

337
00:28:35,340 --> 00:28:37,500
He must be full of bragging.

338
00:28:37,500 --> 00:28:38,844
Traitor Ma Su Min.

339
00:28:38,844 --> 00:28:42,528
How does doing the best in his
orchestra make him a traitor?

340
00:28:42,528 --> 00:28:46,351
Have all the fun you want.
The board of directors won't sit quietly.

341
00:28:46,351 --> 00:28:50,895
The embarrassment of the school were
taken to a reputable music festival.

342
00:28:51,429 --> 00:28:54,234
Of course that would cause a ruckus.

343
00:28:54,234 --> 00:28:55,803
What...

344
00:28:57,154 --> 00:28:59,523
Please place your order.

345
00:29:08,545 --> 00:29:11,215
I heard it's a dinner invitation
from Professor Yoon Yi Song?

346
00:29:11,215 --> 00:29:13,962
You're gaining all the
points that we lost.

347
00:29:13,962 --> 00:29:16,372
Of course you're Almighty Cha.

348
00:29:16,372 --> 00:29:18,217
I'm happy to be your fan.

349
00:29:18,217 --> 00:29:20,224
To be supporting you...

350
00:29:20,224 --> 00:29:21,929
Where is Seol Nae Il?

351
00:29:21,929 --> 00:29:25,191
I don't know. She's humming all
the time like she's lost her mind.

352
00:29:25,191 --> 00:29:27,026
She scares me.

353
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:41,446
I definitely feel it's worthwhile
to host a music festival this year.

354
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:43,047
Thank you.

355
00:29:43,047 --> 00:29:47,351
My teacher is not feeling well today...

356
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:50,154
You don't need to hide it.

357
00:29:50,154 --> 00:29:52,374
Don't I know him?

358
00:29:52,374 --> 00:29:55,128
He deserves Maestro's recommendation.

359
00:29:55,128 --> 00:29:58,431
It's just one student.
The rest are the worst.

360
00:29:59,737 --> 00:30:04,020
Without Cha Yoo Jin, I'd have
raised an issue with the school.

361
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:08,305
I don't know why Franz would do that.

362
00:30:08,305 --> 00:30:11,685
I heard he's devoted only to Dean Song.

363
00:30:11,685 --> 00:30:14,124
Wouldn't that be the reason?

364
00:30:14,124 --> 00:30:15,479
I wouldn't know.

365
00:30:15,479 --> 00:30:18,282
The violinist whose
competency is at the bottom.

366
00:30:18,282 --> 00:30:20,612
The timpanist with excessive excitement.

367
00:30:20,612 --> 00:30:23,824
Besides, the pianist who is
slow in reading the score.

368
00:30:23,824 --> 00:30:26,156
Why did he recommend them?

369
00:30:26,156 --> 00:30:28,784
Especially that Seol Nae Il.

370
00:30:28,784 --> 00:30:32,082
How could she run out after
a few words of scolding?

371
00:30:32,082 --> 00:30:35,717
That's why all the music students
get a bad reputation.

372
00:30:38,463 --> 00:30:40,698
First, your hand...

373
00:30:47,139 --> 00:30:50,834
Every one of them is the
worst without foundation.

374
00:30:50,834 --> 00:30:52,869
They are not the worst.

375
00:30:53,854 --> 00:30:56,104
His competency might be at the bottom

376
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:58,859
the violinist enjoys music
with full emotions.

377
00:30:58,859 --> 00:31:04,533
The timpanist might be overly
excited, but he is very hardworking.

378
00:31:05,365 --> 00:31:08,134
It's not that she doesn't want to play...

379
00:31:09,536 --> 00:31:14,874
she's a pianist who enjoys the
piano with an innocent mind.

380
00:31:18,014 --> 00:31:21,084
I'm sorry. I'll be going.

381
00:32:02,256 --> 00:32:05,422
The cafeteria, the store and the cafe...

382
00:32:05,422 --> 00:32:07,724
If she's not at the
convenience store either...

383
00:32:08,303 --> 00:32:10,571
where would Seol Nae Il go?

384
00:32:34,079 --> 00:32:38,208
Professor, do you not
have time today either?

385
00:32:38,208 --> 00:32:39,632
I won't take much time.

386
00:32:39,632 --> 00:32:41,434
My goodness.

387
00:32:42,629 --> 00:32:45,142
You have time to follow me around.

388
00:32:45,142 --> 00:32:48,411
You must have a lot of time,
Mr. Lee Yoon Hoo.

389
00:32:50,053 --> 00:32:55,292
Now you're not playing the cello,
you must have too much time.

390
00:32:57,311 --> 00:33:00,384
Do what you want to do.

391
00:33:00,384 --> 00:33:02,686
Until you want to do it again.

392
00:33:16,413 --> 00:33:19,092
Even if I do what I want to do,

393
00:33:19,092 --> 00:33:21,009
I don't want to do it...

394
00:33:22,377 --> 00:33:24,579
Then what should I do, Professor?

395
00:34:28,277 --> 00:34:30,170
It's fast.

396
00:34:30,170 --> 00:34:33,073
I feel like I'm listening
to Richter's performance.

397
00:34:34,032 --> 00:34:36,567
Is it possible to play this fast?

398
00:34:37,744 --> 00:34:41,948
No, this is not just
because of fast speed.

399
00:34:46,202 --> 00:34:47,972
Jeax d'eau (Playing Water).

400
00:34:47,972 --> 00:34:49,673
I want to play it too.

401
00:34:57,501 --> 00:35:00,804
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to sneak in.

402
00:35:17,784 --> 00:35:22,015
It's okay, I snuck in here to play, too.

403
00:35:24,333 --> 00:35:29,104
By the way, why are you playing
alone, not at an evaluation?

404
00:35:53,984 --> 00:35:55,374
Orabang!

405
00:35:56,719 --> 00:35:59,588
Orabang, I had an evaluation.

406
00:36:01,537 --> 00:36:05,207
I did it by myself, but I did well.

407
00:36:05,207 --> 00:36:07,108
I really worked hard.

408
00:36:10,128 --> 00:36:13,030
- Orabang, I...
- Stop right there.

409
00:36:18,368 --> 00:36:20,102
Don't follow me.

410
00:36:20,848 --> 00:36:23,647
Why do you make me worry
so much about you?

411
00:36:23,647 --> 00:36:26,627
Why do you keep following me around
and turn my insides upside down?

412
00:36:34,736 --> 00:36:36,204
Orabang...

413
00:36:37,287 --> 00:36:42,492
Sunbae, did I do something wrong?

414
00:36:44,746 --> 00:36:47,361
Did I really make you upset?

415
00:36:52,376 --> 00:36:54,811
I don't know what this is about...

416
00:36:56,550 --> 00:36:58,118
but I'm sorry.

417
00:37:06,556 --> 00:37:07,856
Come here.

418
00:37:41,929 --> 00:37:43,697
Don't get too excited.

419
00:37:44,723 --> 00:37:48,738
It's cold outside... and it's dark.

420
00:37:48,738 --> 00:37:50,540
You might fall over.

421
00:37:51,147 --> 00:37:53,616
This is only because you might
scrape your knees again.

422
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:59,612
I heard you ran away
from your first class.

423
00:38:34,273 --> 00:38:36,773
Number five in my bucket list.

424
00:38:36,773 --> 00:38:41,321
Play the cello as long as
my fingers allow me.

425
00:38:50,289 --> 00:38:55,169
That timpanist was famous, but
couldn't understand how I felt at all.

426
00:38:55,169 --> 00:38:57,629
You're just too ahead of your time!
Don't worry!

427
00:38:57,629 --> 00:38:58,955
He's right!

428
00:38:58,955 --> 00:39:00,551
Thank you.

429
00:39:00,551 --> 00:39:03,420
- Music is for fun.
- Let's go!

430
00:39:04,341 --> 00:39:06,729
Please! Be quiet!

431
00:39:06,729 --> 00:39:09,098
Talk about your war stories
when you get home, okay?

432
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:11,894
Seol Nae Il, eat that.

433
00:39:11,894 --> 00:39:14,162
Keep quiet while you're eating!

434
00:39:15,144 --> 00:39:16,553
- Please have this.
- I'm not eating.

435
00:39:16,553 --> 00:39:19,523
Don't give it to him! Don't!

436
00:39:19,523 --> 00:39:21,124
It'll put him to an accident.

437
00:39:29,578 --> 00:39:31,413
Isn't it tough?

438
00:39:31,413 --> 00:39:33,997
I should help you with all these...

439
00:39:33,997 --> 00:39:36,647
It's okay. It's my work.

440
00:39:36,647 --> 00:39:38,170
Tell me if you need help with anything.
I'll help you.

441
00:39:38,170 --> 00:39:41,297
I'll help you with everything.

442
00:39:41,297 --> 00:39:44,037
I've cleaned up the downstairs
Is there anything else I can...

443
00:39:50,557 --> 00:39:52,292
Mini Min Hee!

444
00:39:53,185 --> 00:39:55,478
I bought something for you to eat.

445
00:39:55,478 --> 00:40:00,516
You're such a great friend.
I was starving. Thank you.

446
00:40:05,030 --> 00:40:09,539
Mini Min Hee, are you sure that
Chae Do Kyung is dating the boss's son?

447
00:40:09,539 --> 00:40:13,189
Yes, I can feel it.
She acted like her daughter-in-law.

448
00:40:14,049 --> 00:40:15,584
Great job!

449
00:40:18,752 --> 00:40:22,506
Oh, right. Tell me about the music
festival when I'm done with work today.

450
00:40:22,506 --> 00:40:25,809
A lot of famous people must've came.
Did you learn a lot?

451
00:40:27,511 --> 00:40:31,333
Mini Min Hee, Orabang
said nice things to me.

452
00:40:31,333 --> 00:40:35,465
- He patted my head.
- He did? Here?

453
00:40:35,465 --> 00:40:37,934
- Let me. Please bless me.
- Bless you.

454
00:40:37,934 --> 00:40:39,569
Nae Il, you came.

455
00:40:39,569 --> 00:40:42,205
Who patted your head?

456
00:40:42,818 --> 00:40:44,486
Get back to work.

457
00:40:45,529 --> 00:40:48,863
My Orabang patted my head.

458
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:53,704
And thank you for giving me a vacation.
Thanks to you I had a great trip.

459
00:40:55,552 --> 00:40:57,453
Mini Min Hee!

460
00:40:59,793 --> 00:41:02,129
She's a bit lost...

461
00:41:02,671 --> 00:41:05,273
But as long as she's nice.

462
00:41:08,051 --> 00:41:10,712
What made you decide to go
to Seoul all of a sudden?

463
00:41:10,712 --> 00:41:14,349
Ma'am thinks you're leaving
the country right away.

464
00:41:14,851 --> 00:41:17,153
I found something I want to do.

465
00:41:18,228 --> 00:41:20,263
Something fun.

466
00:41:24,120 --> 00:41:26,526
Number six in my bucket list.

467
00:41:26,526 --> 00:41:30,741
Date an odd girl that
I've never met before.

468
00:41:33,897 --> 00:41:36,999
You're called a genius
cellist, Yoon Hoo.

469
00:41:36,999 --> 00:41:42,238
You don't need to come to Han Eum
as an exchange student.

470
00:41:42,794 --> 00:41:44,364
You're too kind.

471
00:41:44,364 --> 00:41:47,716
If it's too much, please accept
me as an audit student for now.

472
00:41:47,716 --> 00:41:50,486
Of course we'll welcome you.

473
00:41:50,486 --> 00:41:56,225
But there should be no reason to come
to Han Eum as a Juilliard student.

474
00:41:58,894 --> 00:42:02,263
I'm tired of competitions.

475
00:42:04,191 --> 00:42:08,418
At least once, I want
to enjoy music with

476
00:42:08,418 --> 00:42:10,598
people around my age,
and not compete with them.

477
00:42:30,759 --> 00:42:32,339
You have something on your face.

478
00:42:38,261 --> 00:42:39,695
Here.

479
00:42:40,394 --> 00:42:42,479
This tastes so good

480
00:42:42,479 --> 00:42:45,582
Those damn... they came again.

481
00:42:46,275 --> 00:42:49,144
I can't kick out customers...

482
00:42:50,779 --> 00:42:52,936
- Who?
- Who are You talking about?

483
00:42:52,936 --> 00:42:56,657
That girl who made my
bandmaster son feel so small.

484
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:58,441
Do you think anyone with long hair
is a woman?

485
00:42:58,441 --> 00:43:01,911
A woman should be nice and soft.

486
00:43:02,612 --> 00:43:05,548
See? See? She always leads men.

487
00:43:05,548 --> 00:43:08,839
We had a match between
orchestras, so we had no choice.

488
00:43:08,839 --> 00:43:10,174
Anyways!

489
00:43:12,455 --> 00:43:17,193
My son, you should go practice!

490
00:43:19,057 --> 00:43:21,751
It's been a while since I came here.
Let me earn my keep.

491
00:43:21,751 --> 00:43:23,799
This is for Table 20, right?

492
00:43:26,565 --> 00:43:29,234
My son, you might fall over.
Careful, careful...

493
00:43:30,194 --> 00:43:33,789
My son, you're earning
your keep by breathing.

494
00:43:33,789 --> 00:43:36,091
- What are you doing?
- It hurts.

495
00:43:45,959 --> 00:43:48,662
Yoo Il Lak! Why are you here?

496
00:43:51,427 --> 00:43:55,364
I have something to tell you.

497
00:43:58,228 --> 00:44:00,196
It's okay. Tell me.

498
00:44:13,150 --> 00:44:14,918
What's wrong with him?

499
00:44:14,918 --> 00:44:17,282
- Like a pervert.
- Right?

500
00:44:17,282 --> 00:44:18,825
What did he say?

501
00:44:18,825 --> 00:44:21,494
He said he's not a pervert.

502
00:44:23,338 --> 00:44:24,773
Let's eat.

503
00:44:33,950 --> 00:44:35,551
She's pretty.

504
00:44:40,803 --> 00:44:43,973
This is an official complaint
from Yoon Yi Song Music Festival.

505
00:44:45,269 --> 00:44:50,295
Our students must have made an
impression by causing a ruckus.

506
00:44:50,295 --> 00:44:52,455
Especially Seol Nae Il.

507
00:44:52,455 --> 00:44:55,850
She missed all the master classes.

508
00:44:55,850 --> 00:44:57,686
Yoo Il Lak didn't have the competency.

509
00:44:57,686 --> 00:45:01,372
Ma Su Min threw his mallet at his
instructor, and Cha Yoo Jin...

510
00:45:01,372 --> 00:45:03,240
Even Cha Yoo Jin?

511
00:45:06,756 --> 00:45:09,558
The chair of the board plans
to reprimand all of them.

512
00:45:18,414 --> 00:45:20,550
Is everyone here?

513
00:45:23,974 --> 00:45:25,642
What happened?

514
00:45:28,558 --> 00:45:32,395
Hello, Professor von Stresemann.

515
00:45:33,051 --> 00:45:36,632
You took a long time to
decide on your vote.

516
00:45:38,197 --> 00:45:41,567
Then... should I make my decision now?

517
00:45:42,852 --> 00:45:47,410
Should I go for A or S?

518
00:45:47,410 --> 00:45:48,611
Well?

519
00:45:48,611 --> 00:45:53,128
I heard this meeting is for
Cha Yoo Jin and the losers.

520
00:45:53,128 --> 00:45:54,764
Let's take care of that first.

521
00:45:54,764 --> 00:45:58,027
You call your students 'losers'?

522
00:45:58,027 --> 00:46:00,663
Everyone calls them losers.

523
00:46:02,930 --> 00:46:06,868
This meeting is to decide
on the students mentioned

524
00:46:06,868 --> 00:46:09,137
in the complaint from the music festival.

525
00:46:09,866 --> 00:46:14,128
What do you think, as someone
who recommended those students?

526
00:46:14,128 --> 00:46:16,130
Is that true?

527
00:46:17,984 --> 00:46:23,492
Of course they should be
punished if they caused trouble.

528
00:46:24,535 --> 00:46:28,238
But even a school star is up
on the stand for punishment.

529
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:35,003
My... If I knew this would happen,
I shouldn't have let him.

530
00:46:35,003 --> 00:46:37,379
What do you mean?

531
00:46:37,379 --> 00:46:39,414
I'm talking about the interview.

532
00:46:45,430 --> 00:46:47,619
Orabang!

533
00:46:49,893 --> 00:46:53,644
Orabang, I'll take care
of your health from now on.

534
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:56,852
Because you're precious.

535
00:46:56,852 --> 00:46:59,554
Drink it in one gulp.

536
00:47:04,273 --> 00:47:07,109
You look awesome even when you drink.

537
00:47:09,773 --> 00:47:11,141
Quiet.

538
00:47:11,967 --> 00:47:15,204
Stop trespassing in my house.
Leave now.

539
00:47:15,878 --> 00:47:19,249
Okay, okay. After I've eaten breakfast.

540
00:47:19,996 --> 00:47:22,098
Take your time.

541
00:47:28,265 --> 00:47:31,101
Why did this old coot
told me to dress up?

542
00:47:32,382 --> 00:47:33,883
Hold on.

543
00:47:33,883 --> 00:47:36,648
You're a headache.
When did you bring that?

544
00:47:36,648 --> 00:47:38,249
Mr. Cha Yoo Jin!

545
00:47:40,289 --> 00:47:43,417
Hello. I get to see you again.

546
00:47:43,417 --> 00:47:46,553
I'm so glad to see you.
Don't you remember me?

547
00:47:47,582 --> 00:47:51,452
I know. At the Yoon Yi Song Music Festival...

548
00:47:51,452 --> 00:47:54,458
Oh, yes. You interviewed the students.

549
00:47:54,458 --> 00:47:56,585
You do remember.

550
00:47:56,585 --> 00:47:58,670
I'm Reporter Ban Ji Yeon from Modern Classic.

551
00:47:58,670 --> 00:48:01,978
We have an interview location
ready, so why don't we go there?

552
00:48:01,978 --> 00:48:05,007
Excuse me, with my Yoo Jin?

553
00:48:05,007 --> 00:48:09,185
I have no obligation to do interviews
just because I'm Cha Dong Woo's son.

554
00:48:09,185 --> 00:48:12,188
It has nothing to do
with Mr. Cha Dong Woo.

555
00:48:12,689 --> 00:48:16,893
Didn't you hear anything
from Maestro von Stresemann?

556
00:48:18,565 --> 00:48:21,944
He allowed you to be his deputy
to have an interview with me.

557
00:48:21,944 --> 00:48:24,299
- Professor did?
- Milch did?

558
00:48:24,299 --> 00:48:26,601
I heard you're his apprentice.

559
00:48:29,746 --> 00:48:32,815
It should help with commercial success.

560
00:48:33,443 --> 00:48:37,709
As an apprentice of von Stresemann
with his good looks.

561
00:48:37,709 --> 00:48:42,787
Professor, please don't use
such word in education.

562
00:48:43,298 --> 00:48:47,697
Cha Yoo Jin has refused all interviews
as the son of Cha Dong Woo.

563
00:48:47,697 --> 00:48:50,719
But if he would do that for the school

564
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:53,809
I guess we'll have to
reconsider his punishment.

565
00:48:53,809 --> 00:48:57,593
You're fast with your
numbers as a merchant.

566
00:48:57,593 --> 00:49:01,197
Maestro! Don't say such words!

567
00:49:05,612 --> 00:49:10,083
Don't think about doing
business with music anymore.

568
00:49:12,101 --> 00:49:14,203
If you keep messing around...

569
00:49:14,872 --> 00:49:19,843
I'll destroy that honor
you find so precious.

570
00:49:27,926 --> 00:49:30,161
Franz, wait for me!

571
00:49:35,642 --> 00:49:38,311
Mina, because of me...

572
00:49:38,808 --> 00:49:44,189
No. I really hoped that someone
would say that instead of me.

573
00:49:45,191 --> 00:49:48,584
But, Franz, you have to
make a decision now.

574
00:49:48,584 --> 00:49:52,788
If you delay any longer, both
orchestras could be dissolved.

575
00:49:53,536 --> 00:49:59,076
Please tell me if it's S or A.

576
00:49:59,076 --> 00:50:00,677
Mina...

577
00:50:01,371 --> 00:50:04,764
That's not for us to decide.

578
00:50:04,764 --> 00:50:06,302
Franz!

579
00:50:06,302 --> 00:50:09,372
Even if it takes time...

580
00:50:09,372 --> 00:50:14,743
we have to help students
decide on their own.

581
00:50:25,275 --> 00:50:30,138
Professor Do, I really think
I need to remove him.

582
00:50:30,138 --> 00:50:32,558
You mean, Professor von Stresemann?

583
00:50:33,038 --> 00:50:35,244
We'll have to keep him
until the festival.

584
00:50:35,244 --> 00:50:37,805
We can't mess up the students' festival.

585
00:50:37,805 --> 00:50:39,740
Please remove him after that.

586
00:50:40,308 --> 00:50:42,444
I mean, just get rid of him.

587
00:50:54,483 --> 00:50:56,218
What?

588
00:50:56,218 --> 00:50:59,654
Performance? I'll have a piano performance?

589
00:51:00,477 --> 00:51:01,770
Piano?

590
00:51:01,770 --> 00:51:03,105
Yes from me!

591
00:51:03,105 --> 00:51:05,532
His piano performances are really great.

592
00:51:05,532 --> 00:51:07,530
Did the professor really say that?

593
00:51:07,530 --> 00:51:08,986
When?

594
00:51:08,986 --> 00:51:11,288
At the fall festival...

595
00:51:13,237 --> 00:51:15,371
What music am I playing?

596
00:51:15,371 --> 00:51:17,406
Grieg's piano duet.

597
00:51:18,620 --> 00:51:19,868
Who's conducting?

598
00:51:19,868 --> 00:51:24,168
Weren't you going to perform together
with Maestro von Stresemann?

599
00:51:24,999 --> 00:51:27,416
He'll actually conduct?

600
00:51:27,416 --> 00:51:30,219
Together with Milch...

601
00:51:31,341 --> 00:51:33,422
Am I wrong?

602
00:51:33,422 --> 00:51:35,053
I must be mistaken.

603
00:51:35,053 --> 00:51:37,014
Yes, we will.

604
00:51:37,014 --> 00:51:40,075
With Maestro von
Stresemann conducting...

605
00:51:40,075 --> 00:51:41,804
It's a performance not to be missed.

606
00:51:41,804 --> 00:51:45,441
Do you have a girlfriend...

607
00:51:46,398 --> 00:51:49,000
I heard you were doing an
interview, and it's true.

608
00:51:56,658 --> 00:51:57,958
It's been a while.

609
00:52:04,082 --> 00:52:07,261
Seol Nae Il, you're still
good at supporting him.

610
00:52:07,794 --> 00:52:10,013
Who...

611
00:52:10,013 --> 00:52:13,307
Miss Han Eum is his ex-girlfriend.

612
00:52:13,307 --> 00:52:15,701
I am his current girlfriend.

613
00:52:15,701 --> 00:52:17,395
Like this.

614
00:52:17,395 --> 00:52:20,432
I see, Miss Han Eum.

615
00:52:20,432 --> 00:52:23,668
No wonder.
Get both of them in.

616
00:52:25,771 --> 00:52:28,674
Are you really his ex-girlfriend?

617
00:52:31,686 --> 00:52:34,049
Could you leave us for a minute?

618
00:52:34,049 --> 00:52:35,383
Pardon?

619
00:52:37,950 --> 00:52:39,918
Why would I?

620
00:52:41,745 --> 00:52:47,016
No, I should leave. After all
we are only just friends.

621
00:52:48,627 --> 00:52:52,172
I heard you were here, so
I just came to say hello.

622
00:52:52,172 --> 00:52:54,937
Have a good interview.
See you again next time.

623
00:52:54,937 --> 00:52:56,321
Okay.

624
00:52:58,470 --> 00:53:00,219
Go away.

625
00:53:00,219 --> 00:53:04,268
It was such a nice picture with
a handsome guy and a beautiful girl.

626
00:53:07,187 --> 00:53:11,424
Warm and even cool.

627
00:53:13,360 --> 00:53:17,361
She's perfect for Il Lak.

628
00:53:17,361 --> 00:53:23,245
It's better to exclude your subjective
tempo from your young spirit.

629
00:53:24,140 --> 00:53:27,716
The composer's intentions,
performance style...

630
00:53:27,716 --> 00:53:32,346
above all, it's very
important to identify

631
00:53:32,346 --> 00:53:35,582
the pace that orchestra
members can follow.

632
00:53:36,258 --> 00:53:38,844
It's also important to
manage your health.

633
00:53:38,844 --> 00:53:43,307
A composer's pace can be disheveled once
he gets drunk and his pulse increases...

634
00:53:43,307 --> 00:53:48,378
I see. I'll be careful about drinking.

635
00:53:50,731 --> 00:53:55,535
If you live a boring life like Viera,
your music will also become stuffy.

636
00:53:56,078 --> 00:54:00,324
People say Teacher Viera's music
has deepened with his experience.

637
00:54:00,324 --> 00:54:03,160
With his age,
his pulse slowed down,

638
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,395
so his music must have
slowed down, too.

639
00:54:10,417 --> 00:54:13,119
I am an exception.

640
00:54:13,629 --> 00:54:17,099
It's not that I got old,
I became mature.

641
00:54:18,050 --> 00:54:19,918
Sure, sure.

642
00:54:22,971 --> 00:54:26,102
You can't be thinking
that a conductor goes up on

643
00:54:26,102 --> 00:54:33,315
the podium to look down
on the orchestra members, right?

644
00:54:33,315 --> 00:54:37,473
It's for the purpose of
seeing the members well.

645
00:54:37,473 --> 00:54:41,677
If you know that,
you should learn to be humble first.

646
00:54:56,964 --> 00:55:03,800
If you were me... which
orchestra would you choose?

647
00:55:03,800 --> 00:55:09,351
- Pardon?
- Is it A that has tradition, effort and talent?

648
00:55:10,573 --> 00:55:16,411
Or is it S that has a free spirit?

649
00:55:19,561 --> 00:55:22,197
Think about it.

650
00:55:28,412 --> 00:55:30,881
I have a test soon...

651
00:55:32,708 --> 00:55:35,044
Why are there so much to memorize?

652
00:55:36,257 --> 00:55:39,193
What's taking him so long?

653
00:55:41,008 --> 00:55:44,978
What? I don't get any of this.

654
00:55:56,051 --> 00:55:59,321
Sunbae, please help me with my studies.

655
00:55:59,321 --> 00:56:03,947
I have to take a test,
but I think I'll flunk.

656
00:56:03,947 --> 00:56:07,083
What do I do? I can't fail.

657
00:56:09,411 --> 00:56:12,400
Which orchestra is right?

658
00:56:12,400 --> 00:56:16,537
No, is there a right way in music?

659
00:56:17,961 --> 00:56:21,510
Classical music prides itself
in the most beautiful, perfect harmony

660
00:56:21,510 --> 00:56:25,300
when it's played as a whole.

661
00:56:25,300 --> 00:56:30,733
Meticulously calculated perfect
sound is created as promised.

662
00:56:30,733 --> 00:56:33,852
My interpretation is also on that track.

663
00:56:33,852 --> 00:56:41,193
But... is the music that can't communicate
with people worth anything?

664
00:56:41,193 --> 00:56:44,255
Authentic classical music
that refuses free styling

665
00:56:44,255 --> 00:56:47,491
was also created based on the
current trend at the time.

666
00:56:48,804 --> 00:56:51,406
So, after dinner,
we can study together...

667
00:56:54,786 --> 00:56:58,080
Sunbae! Sunbae!

668
00:56:58,080 --> 00:57:00,883
Wait a minute. I'm thinking right now.

669
00:57:03,549 --> 00:57:07,019
You're always thinking these days.
You don't hang out with me anymore.

670
00:57:09,596 --> 00:57:13,099
- What do you want to eat today?
- Keep quiet for a minute.

671
00:57:24,653 --> 00:57:27,456
I'll forgive you if you come
back by the time I count to three.

672
00:57:29,032 --> 00:57:30,667
One.

673
00:57:31,785 --> 00:57:33,704
Two!

674
00:57:33,704 --> 00:57:35,305
Two and a half!

675
00:57:37,386 --> 00:57:39,454
Two and a half and a quarter.

676
00:57:42,171 --> 00:57:44,292
I'm almost at three.

677
00:57:44,292 --> 00:57:47,629
You two... haven't changed at all.

678
00:58:05,652 --> 00:58:08,355
You probably didn't miss me.

679
00:58:10,032 --> 00:58:14,036
Didn't you... miss me?
